Here we must stop, and see how these two authors do agree. For, according to Strabo's account, one thousand three hundred furlongs‚ and a little more, run out from Pelu- sium to J oppa: that is, one hundred and sixty three miles, or thereabouts: but according to Pliny's‚ at first sight, more by sar.
